<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1189,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,463,1349,1375]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Description.</emphasis>
General color pale yellowish in alcohol, possibly greenish in life. Eyes with unpigmented mesal area (
<figureCitation box="[624,695,1389,1415]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[264,383,1525,1549]" captionTargetBox="[429,1160,521,1471]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[418,1169,492,1522]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Macrogynoplax matogrossensis sp. n. male. Fig. 8, head and pronotum; Fig. 9, sternum 9; Fig. 10, penial armature lateral view; Fig 11, ventral view; Fig. 12, dorsal view. Scales: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170546/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[679,695,1389,1415]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wings pale, in a few specimens darker area at anastomosis and CuA.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1189,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,382,1469,1495]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Male.</emphasis>
Forewing length, 
<quantity box="[614,750,1469,1495]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13–14 mm</quantity>
. Hammer rounded, with horizontal orientation (
<figureCitation box="[273,346,1509,1535]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[264,383,1525,1549]" captionTargetBox="[429,1160,521,1471]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[418,1169,492,1522]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Macrogynoplax matogrossensis sp. n. male. Fig. 8, head and pronotum; Fig. 9, sternum 9; Fig. 10, penial armature lateral view; Fig 11, ventral view; Fig. 12, dorsal view. Scales: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170546/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[329,346,1509,1535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergum 
<number box="[470,499,1509,1535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="10.0">10</number>
with normal pilosity. Penial armature tubular, open ventrally to near apex, ending in a membranous and arched structure; apex membranous, globose; hooks absent; (
<figureCitation box="[363,506,1589,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[264,383,1525,1549]" captionTargetBox="[429,1160,521,1471]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[418,1169,492,1522]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Macrogynoplax matogrossensis sp. n. male. Fig. 8, head and pronotum; Fig. 9, sternum 9; Fig. 10, penial armature lateral view; Fig 11, ventral view; Fig. 12, dorsal view. Scales: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170546/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Figs. 
<number box="[429,506,1589,1615]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Paraprocts with large subapical denticle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1189,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,410,1629,1655]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Female.</emphasis>
Forewing length, 
<quantity box="[636,792,1629,1655]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.475" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.35" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="14.75" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="13.5">13.5–16 mm</quantity>
. Subgenital plate elongate, covering part of sternum 
<number box="[371,400,1669,1695]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="10.0">10</number>
and with a small distal emargination (
<figureCitation box="[885,977,1669,1695]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 14" captionStartId="5.[264,382,632,656]" captionTargetBox="[524,1070,324,613]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[488,1100,296,647]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 14. Macrogynoplax matogrossensis sp. n. female. Fig. 13, sternum 8 and 9; Fig. 14, eggs. Scales: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170547/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[945,977,1669,1695]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Egg oval, 
<number box="[1134,1185,1669,1695]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="0.37">0.37</number>
x 
<quantity box="[1225,1322,1669,1695]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="0.22">0.22mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[273,354,1709,1735]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 14" captionStartId="5.[264,382,632,656]" captionTargetBox="[524,1070,324,613]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[488,1100,296,647]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 14. Macrogynoplax matogrossensis sp. n. female. Fig. 13, sternum 8 and 9; Fig. 14, eggs. Scales: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170547/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[323,354,1709,1735]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1189,1895]" lastBlockId="4.[264,1324,284,430]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,433,1749,1775]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the first named species for west­central 
<collectingCountry box="[1010,1082,1749,1775]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and the first for the State of Mato Grosso. Some nymphs and a female adult, unnamed, were collected in the State of Goiás (
<bibRefCitation author="Bispo" box="[452,664,1829,1855]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" refString="Bispo, P. C., Froehlich, C. G. &amp; Oliveira, L. G. (2002) Stonefly (Plecoptera) fauna in a mountainous area of Central Brazil: composition and adult phenology. Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 19 (Supl. 1), 317 - 323." type="journal article" year="2002">
Bispo et al. 
<number box="[600,664,1829,1855]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The present species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1083,1215,1830,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Macrogynoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[1083,1215,1830,1855]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">M. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ribeiro­ 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira" box="[264,581,1869,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" refString="Ribeiro-Ferreira, A. C. &amp; Froehlich, C. G. (1999) New species of Macrogynoplax Enderlein 1909 from north Brazil (Plecoptera: Perlidae: Acroneuriinae). Aquatic Insects, 21, 133 - 140." type="journal article" year="1999">
Ferreira &amp; Froehlich 
<number box="[520,581,1869,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, from Manaus, Amazonas state, but is larger, as the forewing length of males of 
<taxonomicName box="[482,612,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Macrogynoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[482,612,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">M. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
varies from 
<quantity box="[760,930,284,310]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.125" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.05" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="11.25" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.5">10.5 to 12 mm</quantity>
(personal communication, J.M.F. Ribeiro). Besides, the penial armature of 
<taxonomicName box="[744,874,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Macrogynoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[744,874,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">M. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the ventrally distal arched structure, and the distal membranous part narrows apically, forming a cone. The large subapical denticle of 
<taxonomicName box="[395,614,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Macrogynoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matogrossensis">
<emphasis box="[395,614,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">M. matogrossensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that ilustrated for 
<taxonomicName authority="Froehlich, 2002" authorityName="Froehlich" authorityYear="2002" box="[973,1319,404,430]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Macrogynoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[973,1103,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">M. pulchra</emphasis>
(Froehlich, 
<number box="[1247,1311,404,430]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
